<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Heavily" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Heavily,</orth> 1) so as to press down, grievously: <cit><quote>how h. this befell to the poor gentlewoman,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.226" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 226</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h. punished,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 155</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the tidings which I have h. borne,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.182" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 182</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) sorrowfully, mournfully: <cit><quote>and h. tell o'er the sad account,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 30.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 30, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>which h. he answers with a groan,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.50.11" default="NO" valid="yes">50, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 3, 18</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.309" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 309</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>